                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_cwan_2" n="2" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>cwan</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ciwan</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>чугун</q></tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">в иронском только в сложении <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cwajnag"/> (из %icwan-ag%i) ‘чугунный котел’</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">in Iron it is found only in compound <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cwajnag"/> (from %icwan-ag%i) ‘cast iron kettle’</note><tr xml:lang="en"><q>cast iron</q></tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">в иронском только в сложении <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cwajnag"/> (из %icwan-ag%i) ‘чугунный котел’</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">in Iron it is found only in compound <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cwajnag"/> (from %icwan-ag%i) ‘cast iron kettle’</note></sense><re><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">сюда же</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">also here</note><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>cwancʼу</orth><form type="variant"><orth>swancʼy</orth></form></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ciwancʼi</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>подставка для котелка</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>pot stand</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>таган</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>tivet</q></tr></sense></sense></re><exampleGrp><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>wærtæ eci ciwan xed ka ʽj, obælti ærbacæwuj izæræj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>вон тот чугунный мост, по нему он приходит вечером</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>that cast-iron bridge over there, he comes across it in the evening</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Диг._сказ."/><biblScope>17</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>ku raxælewtæ ʽj i ciwan agæj... i tævdæ basæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>расплескался из чугунного котла горячий суп</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>hot soup spilled out from a cast iron kettle</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>83</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>cwajnaǵy wælqūs arxajy jæ artyl īw sawdaræg ūs</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>у котла возится над огнем женщина в трауре</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>a woman in mourning bothers with fire nearby the kettle</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>43</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>wærtæ eci ciwan xed ka ʽj, obælti ærbacæwuj izæræj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>вон тот чугунный мост, по нему он приходит вечером</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>that cast-iron bridge over there, he comes across it in the evening</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Диг._сказ."/><biblScope>17</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>ku raxælewtæ ʽj i ciwan agæj... i tævdæ basæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>расплескался из чугунного котла горячий суп</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>hot soup spilled out from a cast iron kettle</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>83</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>cwajnaǵy wælqūs arxajy jæ artyl īw sawdaræg ūs</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>у котла возится над огнем женщина в трауре</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>a woman in mourning bothers with fire nearby the kettle</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>43</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Тюркское слово, широко распространенное в кавказских языках: <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>čojun</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w>čuhun</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w>čüjün</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>čudan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><lang/> <w>čuvani</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><w>čivani</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="lzz"><lang/> <w>čuveni</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="lzz"><w>čoǧeni</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ka-x-dial"><lang/> <w>čoina</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Беридзе"/></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Беридзе"/></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sva"><lang/> <w>čweni</w> <gloss><q>котел</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/> <w>čojen</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/> <w>čuon</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><w>čon</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><w>čuina</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>šuan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="uby"><lang/> <w>čuwan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>čwan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="abq"><lang/> <w>čuan</w></mentioned>.<mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>чугун</w></mentioned> относится сюда же. В дигорском диалекте сохранилась форма, более близкая к русской: <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/> <w>cigon</w> <gloss><q>чугунный котелок</q></gloss></mentioned>. Значения ‘чугун’ и ‘котел’ повсюду переплетаются.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">A turkic word widespread in Caucasian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>čojun</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w>čuhun</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w>čüjün</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>čudan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><lang/> <w>čuvani</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><w>čivani</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="lzz"><lang/> <w>čuveni</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="lzz"><w>čoǧeni</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ka-x-dial"><lang/> <w>čoina</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Беридзе"/></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Беридзе"/></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sva"><lang/> <w>čweni</w> <gloss><q>kettle</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/> <w>čojen</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/> <w>čuon</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><w>čon</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><w>čuina</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>šuan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="uby"><lang/> <w>čuwan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>čwan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="abq"><lang/> <w>čuan</w></mentioned>.<mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>čugun</w></mentioned> refers here. In Digor there is a form which more close to the Russian one: <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/> <w>cigon</w> <gloss><q>cast iron little kettle</q></gloss></mentioned>. Meanings ‘cast iron’ and ‘kettle’ interwine everywhere.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>